'''Mitake Shrine''' (御嶽神社, Mitake Jinja) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Sakuragawa (Itabashi)|Sakuragawa]], [[Itabashi|Itabashi Ward]], [[Tokyo]]. It is also known by the locality names '''Sakuragawa Mitake Shrine''' and '''Kami-Itabashi Mitake Shrine'''.

== Overview ==
The exact founding date is unknown. Historically, there were no public shrines in the area, only a private {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft}} belonging to the Takarada family, who relocated here after being forced to move during the construction of {{ill|Edo Castle|ja|江戸城|12=draft}} by {{ill|Ōta Dōkan|ja|太田道灌|12=draft}} in the mid-[[15th century]]. Therefore, a public shrine was established by inviting a divided spirit (bunrei) either from {{ill|Musashi-Mitake Shrine|ja|武蔵御嶽神社|12=draft}} or {{ill|Kana Sakura Shrine|ja|金櫻神社|12=draft}}.<ref name="jinja">Itabashi Ward Board of Education, "Itabashi no Jinja (Cultural Properties Series Vol.36)," Itabashi Ward Board of Education, 1981, pp. 89-90.</ref>

Every year on [[March 8]], a ritual called the "Bisha Festival" is held, in which decorations of cranes and turtles made of [[Daikon]] radishes are offered with heaps of rice.<ref name="jinja" />

<gallery>
File:Mitake-jinja hall of worship 2022-11-13.jpg|Haiden (worship hall)
</gallery>

== Subordinate Shrines ==
* Inari Shrine
* Shinmei Shrine

== Ujiko (Parishioner) Area ==
* Part of [[Sakuragawa (Itabashi)|Sakuragawa]] 1-chome
* [[Kami-Itabashi]] 1-3 chome

== Access ==
* 11-minute walk from [[Kami-Itabashi Station]].

